import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Miles_per_Gallon'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Weight_in_lbs'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Weight_in_lbs'], errors='coerce')
    data['Miles_per_Gallon'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], data['Weight_in_lbs'])
    plt.title('How does the weight of the cars vary with their Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Weight_in_lbs')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Horsepower'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Horsepower'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Horsepower'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['Horsepower'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['Horsepower'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Horsepower'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Horsepower?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Cylinders'] = data['Cylinders'].astype(int)
    chart_data = data[['Acceleration', 'Cylinders']]
    chart_data.boxplot(by='Cylinders')
    plt.title('How does the acceleration of the cars vary with their Cylinders?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Cylinders')
    plt.ylabel('Acceleration')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
